      'Reappointment March 2028 under what is likely still a Democratic GA. Real institutional pressure for an off-ramp.',
    ],
    flip: 'A McCullough vote signal toward the 1912 deference line is the single most important thing to watch. If he goes that way, the strike collapses.',
  },
  {
    id: 'russell',
    name: 'Wesley G. Russell Jr.',
    role: 'Associate Justice',
    appointer: 'Divided GA, 2022 (Republican-side pick)',
    termEnds: 'Jun 30, 2034',
    retirement: '~2043',
    leanIndex: 2,
    call: 'Strike (lean)',
    confidence: 'Medium-High',
    color: '#9b2233',
    bench: 'Conservative',
    chair: 3,
