            <div class="pressure-note">
              <h5>The 144-year streak</h5>
              <p>
                <b
                  >No Virginia justice has been denied reappointment for
                  partisan reasons since 1883.</b
                > External pressure on Democrats not to retaliate is high — breaking
                the streak for Kelsey, a respected jurist with no ethical complaints,
                would invite legitimate accusations of court-packing. Internal incentive
                for Kelsey to vote his conscience is also high. If they're going to
                retaliate, they're going to retaliate. He may as well write the opinion
                he believes is correct.
              </p>
            </div>
